President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring the third Saturday of each May as Armed Forces Day. In the proclamation, he expresses gratitude to the men and women who serve in the United States Armed Forces and acknowledges their sacrifices in defending the nation and its values. He emphasizes the importance of supporting and taking care of the troops and their families, stating that the strength of the country is measured by how it supports them. The proclamation encourages appropriate observances of Armed Forces Day and invites governors, officials, veterans, civic leaders, and organizations to participate in the observance. It also calls upon all Americans to display the flag of the United States at their homes on Armed Forces Day and to learn more about military service and volunteer at organizations that support the troops and their families.